# CSRF where token validation depends on request method

## Vulnerability Type
CSRF	

## Difficulty
appara

## Platform
PortSwigger Web Security Academy

## Goal
To solve the lab, craft some HTML that uses a CSRF attack to change the viewer's email address and upload it to your exploit server

## Root Cause
This lab's email change functionality is vulnerable to CSRF. It attempts to block CSRF attacks, but only applies defenses to certain types of requests.

## Exploitation Steps
1. Browse the application  
2. login with provided credentials  
3. intercept email change request  
4. in repeater tab observe CSRF token (if you change it, error will come)  
5. change the request method  
6. go to engagement tools and generate CSRF PoC  
7. go to exploit server then deliver to victim  

## Impact
An attacker can change user email address  

## What I Learned
in this lab i learned is how to change victim email  
